The paper deals with deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their performance in tasks such as image classification, object detection, and image segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses pruning filters from CNNs, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the plasticity of deep neural networks, which is a topic in artificial intelligence and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the pruned networks, which involves metrics and evaluation techniques commonly used in natural language processing, falling under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the pruned networks, which involves optimization techniques and algorithms commonly used in neural networks, falling under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
